<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="attitude-n">attitude <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ætɪtjuːd/    美 /'ætɪtuːd/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>态度；看法：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>have / take / adopt a positive attitude</strong>
采取积极的态度</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everything depends on people’s attitude. / Attitude is everything.
态度决定一切。</p><footer>2014 江西书面表达改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>attitude to / towards:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We should develop a good attitude to life.
我们应该树立良好的生活态度。</p><footer>2008 辽宁书面表达</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>姿势：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He knelt in an attitude of prayer. 
他以祈祷的姿势跪着。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Despite such a big difference in <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (对…的态度) what one eats, there is no doubt that people in the west regard the Chinese food as something special  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. attitude towards / to  </p></div>